summary:
Chez Circul'R, nous croyons au pouvoir de la collaboration pour permettre l’émergence d’un modèle fondé sur l’équilibre entre enjeux économiques et respect des limites planétaires. 

Pour créer les conditions de ce futur souhaitable, nous plaçons notre expertise et celle de notre écosystème au service de la transition des entreprises et des territoires vers une économie circulaire. 

Nous intervenons à toutes les étapes de la transition :

1/ Sensibilisation et formation des équipes
2/ Conseil dans la mise en œuvre de projets concrets
3/ Création et animation de communautés

Pour en savoir plus : https://www.circul-r.com/

We aim to explore and demonstrate how to create economies that meet the needs of all people within the means of the living planet, to empower others in bringing about this transformational change, and so help to realize a regenerative and distributive economic future. 

NGO website: https://doughnuteconomics.org/'}, {'date': {'start': {'month': 3, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}, 'end': {'month': 10, 'day': None, 'year': 2022}}, 'role': 'Volunteer', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'Le Refettorio Paris', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D0BAQEDBScN744XrQ/company-logo_400_400/0/1588173734978?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=lZrdFNjZb-C9CHJHY03Da6TY5MyF-gCynUWLefjM8HE', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/refettorio-paris/'}, 'cause': 'SOCIAL_SERVICES', 'description': 'Refettorio Paris is an inspiring community kitchen located in the crypt of the church of la Madeleine, in the heart of Paris.

It offers a welcoming dinnertime food service to people in situations of social vulnerability transforming surplus ingredients - that would otherwise be wasted - into delicious meals.

Refettorio Paris is not a charity project, it’s a cultural one.
By involving artists, architects and designers we want to create an engaging and inspiring space where people in situations of social vulnerability, as well as the whole community, can feel valued and welcome.

NGO website: https://refettorioparis.com/'}, {'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2014}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2015}}, 'role': 'Student Tutor', 'company': {'id': None, 'name': 'Association Socrate', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D0BAQHb_Cw45IrDFg/company-logo_400_400/0/1536942921457?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=T2q8wId4xByx5djAfFvKCbNhvuRfDB5PLq2C2v4gCvc', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/association-socrate/'}, 'cause': 'EDUCATION', 'description': 'Socrate aims to prevent primary and secondary school students (7-14 years old) from dropping out of school through the organization of mentoring pairs by volunteer high school students.
It also aims to encourage the commitment of high school students (15-18 years old) by offering them civic and solidarity action based on school support.
By encouraging the transmission of experiences between peers, the Socrate workshops promote the transition from primary to secondary school and from secondary to high school, as well as social and academic diversity.
The facilitators encourage parents in their relations with the educational teams and in their own school monitoring functions and direct them to local social and associative third parties.
The association completes its program by organizing cultural activities for children, high school volunteers, and their families. 

NGO website: http://www.associationsocrate.org/'}]
